<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,899,1511]" box="[151,647,899,924]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,475,899,924]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371">Length (including tegmen).</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity box="[554,643,899,923]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,899,1511]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371">
Body yellowish, with dark brownish bands; head black, pronotum and scutellum greenish; pronotum with two separated smoky markings in middle; forewings light golden yellow, clavus smoky, veins yellow. Head as broad as pronotum, anterior margin of vertex produced obtuse angle, midlength longer than next to eyes. Pronotum short, 
<number box="[151,200,1043,1068]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="1.25">1.25</number>
times length of vertex; scutellum as long as vertex. Forewings elongate, exceeding the abdomen, with distinct appendix and 
<number box="[308,322,1079,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
anteapical cells and 
<number box="[555,569,1079,1103]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
apical cells.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,899,1511]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371">
Male abdomen. 
<number box="[382,396,1118,1142]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
nd acrotergite with trunk widely V-shaped; neck slender, shorter than half of trunk width. 
<number box="[1406,1420,1118,1142]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodeme exceeding 
<number box="[463,477,1157,1181]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[487,499,1157,1181]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="3.0">3</number>
of tergite posteriorly. 
<number box="[766,780,1157,1181]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="1.0">1</number>
st sternal apodeme with anterior lobes elongate, rounded apically, about twice as long as wide; posterior lobes strikingly reduced. 
<number box="[980,994,1196,1220]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.0">2</number>
nd sternal apodeme with posterior lobes about 
<number box="[220,255,1231,1256]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,899,1511]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371">
Male genitalia. Pygofer with a caudo-ventral tubercle. Subgenital plates with uniseriate macrosetae on outer margin. 
<number box="[249,277,1306,1330]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="10.0">10</number>
th abdominal segment membranous. Style short, with small teeth on medial margin. Connective Yshaped, stem nearly the same as arms. Aedeagus slender, bifurcated at 
<number box="[977,1012,1343,1367]" pageId="10" pageNumber="371" value="0.4">0.4</number>
times length of shaft and crossed at middle, gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
